29.0, 1058.4, 547.4]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [1073.3, 529.0, 1081.6, 547.4]}, {"text": "—", "bbox": [1129.2, 529.0, 1145.8, 547.4]}, {"text": "Receivables and payables, net (b)", "bbox": [91.7, 555.1, 319.5, 573.5]}, {"text": "29", "bbox": [516.5, 555.1, 533.2, 573.5]}, {"text": "—", "bbox": [866.6, 555.1, 883.2, 573.5]}, {"text": "Total U.K. pension assets", "bbox": [91.7, 579.0, 261.3, 597.4]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [460.6, 579.0, 468.9, 597.4]}, {"text": "7,801", "bbox": [495.6, 579.0, 533.2, 597.4]}, {"text": "8,490", "bbox": [845.7, 579.0, 883.3, 597.4]}, {"text": "(a)", "bbox": [85.4, 632.1, 103.8, 650.5]}, {"text": "In accordance with accounting guidance certain investments that are measured at fair value using the net asset value per share (NAV), or its equivalent,", "bbox": [122.9, 632.1, 1134.4, 650.5]}, {"text": "practical expedient have not been classified in the fair value hierarchy. The fair value amounts presented in the table are intended to permit reconciliation", "bbox": [122.9, 652.1, 1144.1, 670.5]}, {"text": "of the fair value hierarchy to the amounts presented in the statement of financial position.", "bbox": [122.9, 672.1, 718.6, 690.6]}, {"text": "(b)", "bbox": [85.4, 692.2, 104.8, 710.6]}, {"text": "Receivables and payables, net represents amounts for investments sold/purchased but not yet settled along with interest and dividends earned but not yet", "bbox": [122.9, 692.2, 1143.5, 710.6]}, {"text": "received.", "bbox": [122.9, 712.2, 187.9, 730.6]}, {"text": "Except for investments in real estate, the fair value measurements of WPD's pension plan assets are based on the same inputs", "bbox": [85.4, 756.8, 1133.4, 779.9]}, {"text": "and measurement techniques used to measure the U.S. pension plan assets described above.", "bbox": [85.4, 781.8, 854.1, 804.9]}, {"text": "Investments in equity securities represent actively and passively managed funds that are measured against various equity", "bbox": [85.4, 831.8, 1091.9, 854.9]}, {"text": "indices.", "bbox": [85.4, 856.8, 155.0, 879.9]}, {"text": "Other comprises a range of investment strategies, which invest in a variety of assets including equities, bonds, currencies, real", "bbox": [85.4, 906.8, 1135.4, 929.9]}, {"text": "estate and forestry held in unitized funds, which are considered in the Global Tactical Asset Allocation target.", "bbox": [85.4, 931.8, 997.1, 954.9]}, {"text": "U.K. corporate bonds include investment grade corporate bonds of companies from diversified U.K. industries.", "bbox": [85.4, 981.8, 1012.8, 1004.9]}, {"text": "U.K. gilts include gilts, index-linked gilts and swaps intended to track a portion of the plans' liabilities.", "bbox": [85.4, 1031.8, 943.2, 1055.0]}, {"text": "Investments in real estate represent holdings in a U.K. unitized fund that owns and manages U.K. industrial and commercial", "bbox": [85.4, 1081.9, 1120.5, 1105.0]}, {"text": "real estate with a strategy of earning current rental income and achieving capital growth. The fair value measurement of the", "bbox": [85.4, 1106.9, 1114.2, 1130.0]}, {"text": "fund is based upon a net asset value per share, which is based on the value of underlying properties that are independently", "bbox": [85.4, 1131.9, 1101.7, 1155.0]}, {"text": "appraised in accordance with Royal Institution of Chartered Surveyors valuation standards at least annually with quarterly", "bbox": [85.4, 1156.9, 1109.2, 1180.0]}, {"text": "valuation updates based on recent sales of similar properties, leasing levels, prope", "bbox": [85.4, 1181.9, 768.7, 1205.0]}, {"text": "f", "bbox": [428.6, 1181.9, 435.5, 1205.0]}, {"text": "rty operations and/or market conditions. The", "bbox": [768.2, 1181.9, 1144.4, 1205.0]}, {"text": "fund may be subject to redemption restrictions in the unlikely event of a large forced sale in order to ensure other unit holders", "bbox": [85.4, 1206.9, 1137.8, 1230.0]}, {"text": "are not disadvantaged.", "bbox": [85.4, 1231.9, 272.7, 1255.0]}, {"text": "Expected Cash Flows - U.S. Defined Benefit Plans (PPL)", "bbox": [85.4, 1281.8, 635.0, 1305.2]}, {"text": "While PPL's U.S. defined benefit pension plans have the option to utilize available prior year credit balances to meet current", "bbox": [85.4, 1331.9, 1128.0, 1355.0]}, {"text": "and future contribution requirements, PPL contributed $50 million to its U.S. pension plans in January 2019. No additional", "bbox": [85.4, 1356.9, 1110.0, 1380.1]}, {"text": "contributions are expected in 2019.", "bbox": [85.4, 1381.9, 384.2, 1405.1]}, {"text": "PPL sponsors various non-qualified supplemental pension plans for which no assets are segregated from corporate assets. PPL", "bbox": [85.4, 1432.0, 1143.4, 1455.1]}, {"text": "expects to make approximately $13 million of benefit payments under these plans in 2019.", "bbox": [85.4, 1457.0, 841.7, 1480.1]}]}